It's me.

37
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,960
Did you clean this up too?

38
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:49,800
Officer.

39
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,440
Th-Th-This has n-n-n...

40
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,960
...nothing to do with me, Officer.

41
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,680
Did you clean it up or not?

42
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,440
It was me, but...

43
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,400
...I really didn't know what was inside, Officer.

44
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,200
I'm just responsible for opening and closing up...

45
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,520
...and collecting the recyclables.

46
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,920
Th-Th-Th-That's it.

47
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,080
What time do you clean up?

48
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,520
And where do you usually store them?

49
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:13,960
The bar closed at 5:00 AM today.

50
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,680
After I closed up...

51
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,920
...I just took the cardboard boxes...

52
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:18,560
...and threw them by the trash cans in the back alley.

53
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,080
Take us to have a look.

54
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,480
This way.

55
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:28,960
Here.

56
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,200
That...

57
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,480
...empty bottles...

58
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,120
...and cardboard, I threw right here.

59
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,680
Someone comes to collect them every morning.

60
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:35,760
What time in the morning?

61
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:37,680
No later than ten.

62
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:40,800
Come with me to give a statement.

63
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:47,360
Shen... Shen Man.

64
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,400
The stuff the Team Leader wanted...

65
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,960
...I forgot to make the video.

66
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,080
It's fine, as long as you remember it.

67
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,680
What was I going to say?

68
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,160
Right.

69
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,600
From 5:00 AM to 10:00 AM.

70
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,240
There are several hours in between.

71
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,480
Which means...

72
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:14,480
...the killer had enough time...

73
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,880
...to hide the body in the cardboard boxes.

74
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,520
Making a wish...

75
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,920
...is mostly a spiritual comfort...

76
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:27,000
...for people facing a hard life.

77
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,640
This kind of comfort...

78
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,200
...shouldn't become a tool for the killer...

79
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,640
...to manipulate the ignorance of others.

80
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,520
And it certainly shouldn't become...

81
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,120
...the killer's standard for judging sin.

82
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,080
The killer's MO this time

83
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,560
didn't leave a Demon Idol behind,

84
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,000
but left a card instead.

85
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,800
The pattern on this card

86
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,240
matches the ones on the previous Demon Idols

87
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,320
and can be pieced together.

88
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,000
The pieced-together pattern isn't complete.

89
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,200
The killer is likely to strike again.

90
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,200
The victim's identity is currently undetermined.

91
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,560
The victim's limbs were severed by a blunt instrument.

92
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,400
Time of death appears to be at night,

93
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,000
between 11:00 and 12:00 PM.

94
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,000
In that case,

95
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,040
the killer had enough time

96
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,560
to hide the body.

97
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,240
When the limbs were severed,

98
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,440
the victim was still alive.

99
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,000
The killer deliberately chose a blunt instrument

100
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,680
just to increase the victim's suffering.

101
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:28,240
The time the limbs were sawed off

102
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,560
was earlier than the time of death

103
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,760
by about three days.

104
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,880
Which means

105
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:36,120
the killer kept the victim

106
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,080
locked up somewhere beforehand

107
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,080
to torture them,

108
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,560
and then killed them later.

109
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,760
The cause of death was a skull fracture.

110
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,640
Also,

111
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,000
the body wasn't crushed by a compactor

112
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,000
repeatedly.

113
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,960
Judging by the marks on the victim,

114
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,600
it was likely a heavy truck

115
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,480
that ran over him repeatedly.

116
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,200
How is it going?

117
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,800
Suspicion on the bar staff

118
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,560
